      ```

      ```

      ### Facebook Authentication
      Facebook authentication is carried out via Facebook's OAuth 2.0 methodology. In order to make a Facebook login request use the URL `http://localhost:1337/auth/login?type=facebook`.
      After a valid login is completed, a user will be redirected to `http://localhost:1337/auth/facebook_oauth2?code=SOME-SECRET-CODE`.

      Example Response
      ----------------

      ```
      {
        "auth":{
          "facebookId":"000000000000000000000",
          "name":"John Doe",
          "createdAt":"2014-12-08T03:00:08.208Z",
          "updatedAt":"2014-12-08T03:00:08.239Z",
          "id":1,
          "user":1
        },
        "createdAt":"2014-12-08T03:00:08.232Z",
        "updatedAt":"2014-12-08T03:00:08.232Z",
        "id":1
      }
      ```

